OL,6,FThe so-called operational capacity for
OL,7,FEnglish and Welsh men's and women's
OL,8,Fprisons is 88,822, indicating there is
OL,9,Fnow cell space for 2,733 criminals.
OL,11,FMeanwhile a watchdog found that at HMP
OL,12,FKirkham, in Lancashire, boredom was
OL,13,Fcontributing to the highest drug use
OL,14,Famong open jails in England and Wales
OL,15,F` category prisons with the lowest
OL,16,Flevel of security.
OL,18,FThe men serving time there said they
OL,19,Fwere "frustrated and bored" and many
OL,20,Fwere using drugs, according to chief
OL,21,Finspector of prisons Charlie Taylor.
